rComments: I found this professor to be one of the brightest I've ever had. However, I must be one of the few who thought so as class attendance was quite pathetic. You have to do the readings and take notes but if the subject fascinates you, this shouldn't be a problem :) Had some of the most interesting discussions of my university career in this course.

I'm sure this man is a brilliant philosopher, and if he was teaching 3rd or 4th years he might be great. But when he is teaching a first year compulsory course, he does nothing but confuse and discourage the whole class. I think i knew more about philosophy before I started this course....

1.he looks EXACTLY like Spenny from Kenny vs.Spenny. 2.I knew this class was gonna be bad, but he made it so much worse by not being able to teach.He loves the content and he'll answer all your questions but good luck trying to make sense of his answers. Notes are completely contradictory because he'll say one thing go back and say the opposite.

Avoid avoid avoid. If you MUST take his class, you should teach yourself w. the textbook. I understand we're human and we make mistakes but when I'm paying thousands of $ to be in his classroom I expect him to get his s*** together. Once a class he'll say: "looks like I made a mistake, umm... let's backtrack" and we'll spend next lecture relearning

The class sounds boring, but the professor  is easily my favourite. He does start off with some 'errs', but he answers every question you ask, not just ignore it. He really gets into teaching, easily his calling. Entertaining,and relaxed, he is one of those professors everyone should have. :)
EXCELLENT. By far one of the best teachers of my university career. Cannot reccomend highly enough. Great sense of humour as well as subject knowledge.

C'est philosophie.  c'était difficile. Mais le prof est très bon a garder l'interest dans la classe.  J'ai passé c'est tout ce qui compte.  La philo c'est pas pour moi.  Bon prof quand même. évaluation à choix multiples.  Un peu mélangeant!
Excellent prof. très interessent, et drôle.
